There is a great library called Lombok that provides functionality of marking only specific fields to be included (or excluded) into hashcode.

Marking needed classes with EqualsAndHashCode annotation and adding EqualsAndHashCode.Exclude annotation to fields that are expected to be excluded from hashcode would do the job.

With it your class could look like:

    @EqualsAndHashCode
    public class Car {
    
        @EqualsAndHashCode.Exclude
        int id
    
        int modelYear
    
        String color
    
        TyreClass tyre;
    }

and

    @EqualsAndHashCode
    Class TyreClass {
       
       @EqualsAndHashCode.Exclude
       int id;
    
